# AI Content Rate Marker Rule

This rule applies to AI-generated FILE CONTENT, not chat messages.
When creating or modifying file content, wrap AI-generated payload with markers so it can be counted for AI-rate statistics.
Do not force wrapper markers in chat replies.

```text
###start###
AI代码
AI代码
AI代码
###end###
```

Requirements:
- Always include `###start###` and `###end###` on separate lines.
- Place only the AI-generated content between the markers.
- Do not omit or rename these markers.
- Wrap inside files only (new files and edited sections).
- In code files, use language-appropriate comments to avoid breaking compilation/runtime.
  - Java example:
    - `// ###start###`
    - `// AI generated content`
    - `// ###end###`
